\begin{center}
	{\Large{\bf{CONCLUSION}}}\\
\end{center}
In this project, we will provide an overview of different approaches used for solving travelling salesman problem. The Travelling Salesman Problem (TSP) is a classical combinatorial optimization problem, which is simple to state but very difficult to solve. The problem is to find the shortest tour through a set of N vertices so that each vertex is visited exactly once \cite{taha2011operations}. This problem is known to be NP-hard, and cannot be solved exactly in polynomial time. Many exact and heuristic algorithms have been developed in the field of operations research (OR) to solve this problem. In this project, we will study approaches to solve the travelling salesman problem. 
